Japan's major retailers registered sales of 1.415 trillion yen ($9.94 billion) in August, up 8% from a year earlier, according to the Ministry of International Trade and Industry. 

Retail sales at major department stores were up 8% to 679.1 billion yen, while sales at supermarkets were up 7.9% to 735.7 billion yen. 

A ministry spokeswoman said growing sales of clothing and fresh foods contributed to the August year-to-year growth. 

